      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TREBELLION (3) was kept out of the early speed battle off the wide starting position on the front line last start and failed to run on when ninth over 1740m at Riverina Paceway. Has the benefit of a far better draw. Finds a nice race and can bounce back into winning form. RONZEL SONNY (9) went back last start then worked home in good style to finish 2.5 metres from the winner in second at Forbes over 2060m, adding to his second at Parkes two runs back. Will need an ounce of luck to slot in from this tricky draw. Finds a nice race and will be a major force once more. PYEKAKARIKI (6) has to come into calculations on the back of some strong recent form, most recently when third at this track over 1770m. Must be included. PLATINUMS BOY (7) is in the mix following a respectable third at his most recent appearance over 1710m at Goulburn.",
